{%- endfor %}

{% if show_cybersecurity_guidance %}
CYBERSECURITY EXTRACTION GUIDANCE:
- INCIDENT_ID: Incident identifiers (e.g., INC-2024-0042, CSIRT-IT-001, TKT#9912).
- HASH_FILE: File hashes in MD5, SHA-1, or SHA-256 format (32, 40, or 64 hex characters).
- INTERNAL_SERVER: Internal host/server names used within an organization (e.g., srv-dc01, fileserver-prod).
- IP_ADDRESS: Generic IP address when role is unknown; prefer SOURCE_IP or DESTINATION_IP when context is clear.
- DESTINATION_IP: The target IP address of network traffic or an attack.
- PORT_NUMBER: Network port numbers (e.g., 443, 8080, 3389).
- PROTOCOL: Network protocols (e.g., HTTP, HTTPS, RDP, SMB, DNS).
- USERNAME: Usernames, account names, or login identifiers.
- PASSWORD: Passwords, passphrases, or authentication secrets.
- PROCESS_NAME: Process or executable names (e.g., cmd.exe, powershell.exe, svchost.exe).
- COMMAND: Shell commands, command-line strings, or scripts.

